    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Either set the enum name to be the same as the string you want or, more generally,you can associate arbitrary attributes with your enum values:</p>\n\n<pre><code>enum Strings {\n   STRING_ONE(\"ONE\"), STRING_TWO(\"TWO\");\n   private final String stringValue;\n   Strings(final String s) { stringValue = s; }\n   public String toString() { return stringValue; }\n   // further methods, attributes, etc.\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It's important to have the constants at the top, and the methods/attributes at the bottom.</p>\n"
  }, {
