      "creation_date" : 1408383062,
      "post_id" : 13520581,
      "comment_id" : 39558422,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "This is <i>not</i> an efficient way to do this. This creates a new custom class for every value in the enumeration. In the above example, you&#39;ll see the following in the <code>bin</code> directory: EnumTest$MyType.class EnumTest$MyType$1.class EnumTest$MyType$2.class which will add up <i>real</i> quick. Best to do it as the expected answer, by passing in values to the enum constructor. I actually disagree with overriding <code>toString()</code>; I believe it&#39;s better to use an explicit getter such as <code>getKey()</code> since overriding <code>toString()</code> may be unexpected by another user of the enum."
