    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1473681639,
    "creation_date" : 1473681639,
    "answer_id" : 39449852,
    "question_id" : 3978654,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you <strong>do not</strong> want to use <strong>constructors</strong>, and you want to have a <strong>special name</strong> for the method, try it this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public enum MyType {\n  ONE {\n      public String getDescription() {\n          return \"this is one\";\n      }\n  },    \n  TWO {\n      public String getDescription() {\n          return \"this is two\";\n      }\n  };\n\n  public abstract String getDescription();\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I suspect that this is the <strong>quickest</strong> solution. There is no need to use <strong>variables final</strong>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2901646,
      "reputation" : 2342,
      "user_id" : 3017473,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/cZnTE.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Shohel Rana",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3017473/shohel-rana"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1540319801,
    "last_edit_date" : 1540319801,
    "creation_date" : 1510049037,
    "answer_id" : 47155011,
    "question_id" : 3978654,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use that for string Enum</p>\n\n<pre><code>public enum EnumTest {\n    NAME_ONE(\"Name 1\"),\n    NAME_TWO(\"Name 2\");\n\n    private final String name;\n\n    /**\n     * @param name\n     */\n    private EnumTest(final String name) {\n        this.name = name;\n    }\n\n    public String getName() {\n        return name;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And call from main method</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test {\n    public static void main (String args[]){\n        System.out.println(EnumTest.NAME_ONE.getName());\n        System.out.println(EnumTest.NAME_TWO.getName());\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
